                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12621118" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 9 Aug 2008 04:54:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any interface that references HTD or HCD metadata relies on the cache containing up to date structures, so this blocks work on any client interface for this (e.g. shell, Thrift, or REST).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12621206" author="apurtell" created="Sun, 10 Aug 2008 02:29:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually just always using a MetaScanner in getHTableDescriptor is enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12621207" author="apurtell" created="Sun, 10 Aug 2008 03:06:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Previous patch had linefeed issues that would cause patch to barf.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12621622" author="stack" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2008 21:51:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andrew, does TestTable unit test pass for you?  Fails for me when I apply this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12621623" author="stack" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2008 21:55:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ignore my comment in above. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cleaning and retrying all passed (just takes a while).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12621625" author="stack" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2008 21:58:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch and trunk.  Thanks for the patch Andrew.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
